quest_title: The length of magnet is large compared to its width and breadth. The time period of its oscillation in a vibration magnetometer is 2s. The magnet is cut along its length into three equal parts and three parts. The time period of each part will be
explanation_txt:
We know that \(T=2 \pi \sqrt{\cfrac{I}{M B_{H}}}\)
\(M^{\prime}=\cfrac{M}{3}\)
\(I^{\prime}=\cfrac{1}{12} \cfrac{\mathrm{m}}{3} l^2=\cfrac{1}{3} \times\left(\cfrac{m}{12}l^{2}\right)=\cfrac{\mathrm{I}}{3}\)
\(\cfrac{T^{\prime}}{T}=\sqrt{\cfrac{\mathrm{I}^{\prime}}{\mathrm{M}^{\prime}} \times \cfrac{\mathrm{M}}{\mathrm{I}}}=\sqrt{\cfrac{3 \mathrm{I}}{3 \mathrm{M}} \times \cfrac{\mathrm{M}}{\mathrm{I}}}\)
\(\therefore \quad \mathrm{T}^{\prime}=2 \mathrm{s}\)

So, \(pH = -\log [H^+] = 2\)

explanation_txt:
By Fajans' Rules, compounds are more likely to be ionic if: there is a small positive charge on the cation, the cation is large, and the anion is small.

And, compounds are more likely to be covalent if: there would be a large positive charge on the cation, the cation would be small, and the anion would be large.

explanation_txt:

When a wire is stretched to three times its lengths then area become one third and resistance becomes 9 times

\(\therefore \cfrac{v^{\prime}}{v}=\cfrac{A R}{A^{\prime} R^{\prime}}=\left(\cfrac{A}{\cfrac{A}{3}}\right) \times \cfrac{R}{9 R}=\cfrac{1}{3}\)
\(\therefore \mathrm{v}^{\prime}=\cfrac{v}{3}\)
